<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115H81/1</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Plymouth</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stephens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Plymouth</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 4, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.48 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>American steamer <hi rend="italic">Housatonic</hi>, loaded cargo
                                wheat for British Government, torpedoed by German submarine 12.30,
                                3d instant. Vessel warned and total crew, 37, rescued by submarine
                                and towed for 90 minutes toward land. Submarine fired signal to
                                British patrol boat which subsequently landed crew Penzance.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stephens</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>